      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Current scientific consensus does not support the idea that there are inherent, significant, or actionable biological differences in muscle fiber types or general athletic potential based on race. Genetic variability within any single racial group is far greater than the average difference between groups. Therefore, basing workout programming or client grouping on race is not scientifically supported for optimizing training outcomes. Focus instead on individual fitness assessments, training goals, past experience, and performance metrics to create the most efficient programs for each client.",
