      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get what u mean about individual stuff, but i see coaches talking about certain groups being naturally better at sprinting vs endurance or things like that. like, don't some studies look at specific things like fast-twitch fibers in certain populations? even if there isn’t a \"rule,\" isn't it worth knowing if there are certain trends or tendencies that might make a client more likely to succeed in a specific type of training?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
