      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some studies look at musculoskeletal traits, these findings are highly complex, often debated, and do not translate into simple, reliable generalizations for group training. Attributing athletic talent solely to racial trends oversimplifies incredibly intricate biology and genetics. For practical, ethical, and effective training, it is far more valuable to use functional assessments—like maximal power tests or lactate threshold testing—to determine an individual's physiological profile. These objective measures provide the accurate data needed to structure optimal, personalized training plans.",
      "source": "target",
